cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CL

This paper is about designing graph neural networks using reinforcement learning. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on optimizing the performance of a machine learning model. Additionally, the use of recurrent networks and reinforcement learning suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with neural networks and optimization, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The application of graph neural networks to social and biological data suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
